## Purpose

The purpose of this project is to demonstrate my software development skills in Python, using the django framework. The app will take an input (Social Security number) and run a series of tests and checks on it to try and determine if it is valid and if it belongs to an individual. The app will output where the number belongs to and if it is valid or not.

## Method

The algorithm

A social security number (SSN) is a nine-digit number used by the US Federal government to identify a person.

These numbers are not credentialed by the government; they are issued by the Five-Digit Area Number Authority (FDNAA).

## Example

Example SSN: `456-45-8765`


## Format

A nine-digit number with the following separators:

> The Social Security Number is a nine-digit number that uniquely identifies
> an individual in the United States.

> Source: [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Security_number)

Validator
This package is to validate social security number, a social security number is a string with 13 digits.

npm i ssn-validator
